          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                                        <date>April 20/44</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Dear Friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Aware of your anxi=<lb/>=ety deep interest you
                                        feel in our<lb/> cause the welfare continuation<lb/> of
                                        Judaism I hasten to inform you<lb/> of the result of our law
                                        suit, it<lb/> came on as <sic>apporated</sic> on
                                                  <date>Monday</date><lb/> last continued before the
                                        court until<lb/> last night, when I tell you that but<lb/>
                                        one witness was examined you cannot<lb/> but wonder how it
                                        should have so<lb/> occupied so much time, especially<lb/>
                                        as the Judge ruled out the religious<lb/> questions, but
                                        notwithstanding it was<lb/> incidentally introduced by our
                                        counsel<lb/> the Examination of <persName>Mr.
                                                  Valentine</persName> the<lb/> secretary occupied 2
                                        days, our consul<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr. Memminger</persName> opened the case,
                                        clearly<lb/> extensively did he go into the merits<lb/> not
                                        only in the law but in the changes<lb/> alterations of our
                                        sacred religion, but after<lb/> a patent hearing the judge
                                        decided that<lb/> the religious charity or
                                                  <sic>allecations</sic> could have<lb/> no bearing
                                        on the case that it was altogether<lb/> a matter of Law,
                                        upon that only could the<lb/> case stand, after the
                                        examination of <persName>Mr. V</persName></p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p><persName>Mr. Baily</persName> the opposite counsel declined<lb/>
                                        calling any counsel wherefore had<lb/> to abandon one of the
                                        charges of which<lb/> had been brought collusion fraud<lb/>
                                        by which means he secured the advantage<lb/> of the closing
                                        speech – It is the only<lb/> consolation [?] our [?]<lb/>
                                        left us to know that our <sic>counsellor</sic><lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr Memminger</persName> [?] acquitted [?]<lb/>
                                        with more than the [?] with<lb/> which they have always been
                                        distinguished<lb/> The formers gentleman closing
                                        address<lb/> occupied 5 ½ hours – The charge of the<lb/> [?]
                                        was short but lucid his [?]<lb/> conclusions were that the
                                        Board of trus<lb/>tees were not allowed could not<lb/> meet
                                        without the President that<lb/> no meeting could take place
                                        without<lb/> the consent of the President -<lb/> Of course
                                        such a charge from the<lb/> [?], if even the jury was any
                                        ways<lb/> favourably disposed toward us, settled I<lb/> have
                                        no doubt in their minds any<lb/> doubt or feelings in their
                                        own <sic>judgement</sic><lb/> after [?] our but a little
                                        time<lb/> brought in their verdict against us</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My feelings as well as my friends are of<lb/>
                                        course [?] and to say the least, but<lb/> that is not the
                                        worst, we all now at<lb/> sea again without a pilot, nay
                                        without<lb/> a heaven to steer for, we are in a<lb/>
                                        dreadful situation, we know not what<lb/> is but to do. I
                                        truly regret that you</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>had not been allowed to have come<lb/> or your advice counsel at
                                        this<lb/> moment would have so beneficial<lb/> your
                                        consolation so healing to [?]<lb/> wounded spirits, nay to
                                        the preservation<lb/> of our future prosperity – Your
                                        administration [?] have a great deal to answer for in<lb/>
                                        their indifference to their unfortunate Brethren<lb/> their
                                        sworn religion, they have shown<lb/> thereby favourable to
                                        our opponents by<lb/> their refusal have encouraged them
                                        made<lb/> it apparent that your congregation were
                                        favourable<lb/> [?] views – My feeling will not allow<lb/>
                                        me to carry this better to any extent I<lb/> therefore pray
                                        your continuance of health<lb/> life [?] me to be your
                                        friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">Samuel Hart Sen.</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Please send <persName>Mr. Rosenfeldt</persName> occident by
                                        mail</p>
                              <p>
                                        <persName>I.C. Levy</persName>
                                        <persName>Rev Dr Curtis</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Discontinue</p>
                              <p>I have had several [?] of the Conciliator from
                                                  <placeName>England</placeName>, cost 8 shillings
                                        Sherl[?] Lander [?]<lb/> 42.67 I dont know your agent but if
                                        all the books<lb/> he sends you are in the same proportion.
                                        [?] are dear enough –</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
